# VetClub.ru — Cursor AI Rules
# Frontend: React 19.2, Next.js 16 (App Router), Tailwind CSS, Shadcn UI
# Backend/Data: Supabase, PostgreSQL
# Deployment: Vercel

## Stack
- React 19.2
- Next.js 16 — App Router ONLY (no Pages Router)
- Node.js 24
- Tailwind CSS v4 + Shadcn UI
- PostgreSQL 18.4
- Supabase (auth, database, storage)
- Vercel (deployment, edge functions)

## RULES

### Components
- Always use functional components. No class components.
- Use `'use client'` directive ONLY for components that use hooks (useState, useEffect, useRef, etc.).
- Prefer Server Components by default — no `'use client'` if the component doesn't need client-side interactivity.
- Use `lucide-react` for all icons. Never use other icon libraries.
- Prefer `npx shadcn@latest add <component>` to install Shadcn UI components.

### Data Fetching
- Prefer Server Components for data fetching.
- Use Supabase SSR package (`@supabase/ssr`) for authentication and server-side data access.
- For client-side Supabase, use the browser client from `@supabase/supabase-js`.

### Styling
- Use Tailwind CSS utility classes exclusively. No inline styles, no CSS modules unless absolutely necessary.
- Follow Shadcn UI design system and component patterns.
- Use `cn()` utility (from `clsx` + `tailwind-merge`) for conditional classes.

### Code Style
- Write clean, concise code. Don't explain code unless explicitly asked.
- Use TypeScript strict mode. Always type props and return values.
- Prefer `async/await` over `.then/.catch`.
- Use named exports for components: `export function ComponentName()`.

### API & Backend
- Use Next.js API Routes (`route.ts`) for server endpoints — App Router convention.
- Always set `export const runtime = 'nodejs'` for routes that need filesystem/DB access.
- Use Supabase RPC or direct table queries via Server Components where possible.

### Files & Structure
- Follow App Router structure: `app/page.tsx`, `app/layout.tsx`, `app/loading.tsx`, `app/error.tsx`.
- Keep components in `src/components/` or co-located in `app/` segments.
- Utilities go in `src/lib/`.

### Performance
- Use `React.lazy()` + `Suspense` for code splitting heavy components.
- Prefer static generation (`generateStaticParams`) for pages that don't need dynamic data at request time.
- Use `next/image` for all images with proper `width`/`height` and `alt` attributes.

### Security
- Never expose Supabase `service_role` key in frontend code.
- Use Row Level Security (RLS) policies in Supabase.
- Validate all user inputs on the server side.

### Deployment
- Vercel is the deployment target. Ensure `next.config.js` is compatible.
- Use `vercel env` or dashboard for environment variables — never commit secrets.
- Keep `package.json` engines field aligned with Node.js 24.

### Search (Project Specific)
- The project uses MiniSearch for client-side full-text search.
- Search index is built at build time via `npm run build:search`.
- Index is served as static file `/search-index.json`.
- API Route `/api/search` serves as server-side fallback.

## RESPONSE FORMAT
- Output code only. No explanations unless asked.
- Use TypeScript for all new files.
- Follow existing project patterns and conventions.
